{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7a2c3078-9f50-47a7-9d22-4ef199eccb9a","content":"In .NET MAUI, those `Application`-level overrides are replaced by **`Window` lifecycle events**. The simplest migration path is to subclass `Window`:\n\n```csharp\npublic class MyWindow : Window\n{\n    public MyWindow(Page page) : base(page) { }\n\n    protected override void OnCreated()    // ≈ OnStart\n    {\n        base.OnCreated();\n    }\n\n    protected override void OnDeactivated() // ≈ OnSleep\n    {\n        base.OnDeactivated();\n    }\n\n    protected override void OnResumed()     // ≈ OnResume\n    {\n        base.OnResumed();\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThen return it from your `Application`:\n\n```csharp\npublic partial class App : Application\n{\n    protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n    {\n        return new MyWindow(new MainPage());\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key mappings:**\n| Xamarin.Forms | MAUI Window |\n|---|---|\n| `OnStart` | `OnCreated` |\n| `OnSleep` | `OnDeactivated` / `OnStopped` |\n| `OnResume` | `OnResumed` |\n\nUse `OnStopped` instead of `OnDeactivated` if you only care about the app being fully backgrounded (not just losing focus).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b083f04c-6f85-4c46-aecc-f5346202ab30","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating lifecycle methods from Xamarin.Forms to .NET MAUI. This is a straightforward knowledge question about the MAUI lifecycle API.\n\nIn Xamarin.Forms, you'd override `OnStart`, `OnSleep`, and `OnResume` in your `Application` class. In .NET MAUI, the lifecycle model changed. You now use the `Window` lifecycle events or the `ILifecycleEventHandler` approach.\n\nSpecifically, in .NET MAUI:\n- You can override `CreateWindow` in your `Application` class and subscribe to window lifecycle events\n- Or you can use the platform-specific lifecycle events via `ConfigureLifecycleEvents`\n\n\n- You can also create a custom `Window` class and override its lifecycle methods like `OnCreated`, `OnActivated`, `OnDeactivated`, `OnStopped`, `OnResumed`, and `OnDestroying`, which map to the old Xamarin.Forms lifecycle events. The most direct equivalents are `OnStart` → `Window.Created`, `OnResume` → `Window.Activated`, and `OnSleep` → `Window.Stopped`.","outputTokens":755,"requestId":"503D:1129F2:1CE42FB:1FE91A5:69FA90B1"},"id":"207d13e4-349f-4904-8b81-356265473603","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:52:15.298Z","parentId":"1c6406f2-dd0d-4992-af83-b8bf7c466fee"}
